== List basics == <!--T:2-->

<!--T:3-->
<tvar name=mw>{{ll|MediaWiki}}</tvar> offers three types of lists: '''unordered lists''', '''ordered lists''' and  '''definition''' lists.

=== Basically === <!--T:143-->
</translate>

; <translate><!--T:144--> Unordered lists</translate>
: <translate><!--T:145--> Each item is on a new line starting with an asterisk <code>*</code> e.g. <code>* item</code>.</translate>
; <translate><!--T:146--> Ordered lists</translate>
: <translate><!--T:147--> Each item is on a new line starting with a hash <code>#</code> e.g. <code># item</code>.</translate>
; <translate><!--T:148--> Definition lists</translate>
: <translate><!--T:149--> Each item has two parts: the '''term''' and the '''description'''</translate>
: <translate><!--T:150--> The ''term'' is on a new line starting with a semicolon <code>;</code> e.g. <code>; term</code>.</translate>
: <translate><!--T:151--> The ''description'' follows on the same line after a colon <code>:</code> e.g.<code>; term :  description</code>,</translate>
: <translate><!--T:152--> or the ''description'' starts its own line with a colon <code>:</code> e.g. <code>:  description</code> (there can be several descriptions per term, each one starting with a colon on a new line).</translate>

